Option C) They have complete outer electron shells.  
@INT: Noble gases have complete valence electron shells, which makes them stable and unlikely to react with other elements. This is the primary reason for their chemical inertness.  
@C: High confidence in this being the correct answer.  

Option D) They have extremely high ionization energies only.  
@INT: While noble gases do have high ionization energies, this is related to their complete electron shells. The high ionization energy is a consequence of their stability, not the primary reason for their inertness.  
